1. Initialize git repository
: git init

2. Adding files to the staging area.
: git add .

3. Commit files on the staging area.
: git commit -m "commit message"

4. Push your commits to the remote (github)
: git push -u origin master

5. Adding remote url
: git remote add origin http://www.github.com/<your-repo>.git

6. Check status
: git status

7. Check commit logs
: git log
